query.result:
1 Only the world believed in its peril 2 that beautiful Venus, mad with love, 3 was radiating in the third epicycle;
4 because not only to her did the ancient people 5 in their ancient error do honor with sacrifice and votive cries;
6 but they honored Dione and Cupid, 7 the former as his mother, the latter as her son, 8 and they said that he sat in Dido's lap;
9 and from her from whom I take my beginning 10 they took the name of the star 11 that the sun courts now from its nadir, now from its zenith.

13 I did not notice my ascent into it;
14 but my lady whom I saw grow more beautiful
15 gave me ample proof that I was inside it.

22 No winds descended from a cold cloud, 23 whether visible or not, so swift, 24 that they would not have seemed impeded and slow
25 to one who had seen those divine lights 26 coming toward us, leaving the circle 27 first begun by the high Seraphim;
28 and within those that appeared in front 29 resounded ‘Hosanna’ so that never after 30 was I without the desire to hear it again.

55 You loved me greatly, and you had good reason;
56 for if I had remained on earth, I would have shown you
57 more of my love than just the leaves.

